Algorithm
Define the warehouse graph and heuristic values.
Create an OPEN list using a priority queue.
Insert the start node into the priority queue.
Mark the start node as visited.
Repeat until the priority queue becomes empty:
Remove the node with the smallest heuristic value.
If the current node is the goal node, stop.
Otherwise, expand all neighboring nodes.
For each unvisited neighbor:
Mark it as visited.
Store its parent node.
Insert it into the priority queue according to its heuristic value.
Trace the path from the goal node back to the source.
Display the path found.
